					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not 100% sure, but IIRC, NMIs set the I flag when they fire. This means that as long as the NMI handler is running, IRQs will not fire. Since you have the game logic running inside the NMI, more processing increases the time IRQs are ignored, causing the glitches you're seeing. You could try adding a CLI to the beginning of the NMI handler as a quick fix.</div>

